This paper is about dialogue state tracking, which is a subfield of natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a deep learning approach using recurrent neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing approaches in low resource domains, which could be related to the subfield of software engineering (cs.SD) or neural engineering (cs.NE).
